BY virtue of the king's commission of the peace, oyer and terminer, and goal-delivery of Newgate, holden for the city of London and county of Middlesex, at 




                     Justice-Hall in the Old-Baily, before the Rt. Hon. 


                  William Bridgen, Esq. lord-mayor of the city of London
               ; 


                  Sir Thomas Parker, Knt. lord chief Baron of his majesty's court of exchequer
               ; 


                  Sir Edward Clive, Knt. one of the judges of the court of Common-Pleas
               ; the Hon. Mr. Baron Perrott; 


                  James Eyre, Esq. recorder
               , and others of his majesty's justices of oyer and terminer of the city of London, and justices of goal-delivery of Newgate, holden for the said city and county of Middlesex, on Wednesday the 25th, Thursday the 26th, Friday the 27th, and Saturday the 28th of July, in the fourth year of his majesty's reign, four persons were capitally convicted, for the several crimes in their indictments laid, viz.
